    {
      "id": "l3-articles",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Articles: a, an, the",
      "body": "# a / an / the\n\nHindi has no articles, so English articles need attention.\n\n- **a** / **an** = एक (one, any): *a book* (कोई एक किताब)\n- Use **an** before a **vowel sound**: *an apple*, *an hour* (the *h* is silent).\n- Use **a** before a **consonant sound**: *a book*, *a university* (*university* starts with a *y* sound).\n- **the** = the specific one both speakers know: *the book on the table* (मेज़ पर रखी किताब).\n\nRule of thumb: new thing → *a/an*; already-known thing → *the*."
    },
    {
      "id": "l3-ex-match-articles",
      "type": "exercise",
      "theory_ref": "l3-articles",
      "title": "Match the articles",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l3-ex-match-articles",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each English article with its use.",
        "card_ids": [
          "hi-art-a",
          "hi-art-an",
          "hi-art-the"
        ],
        "pairs": [
          {
            "left": "a",
            "right": "एक (व्यंजन से पहले)"
          },
          {
            "left": "an",
            "right": "एक (स्वर से पहले)"
          },
          {
            "left": "the",
            "right": "निश्चित आर्टिकल"
          }
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
